<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1047" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1047">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Griscom</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May 19,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Hay states that the President is confident that His Majesty the
                            Sultan will keep the promise so long ago made to pay indemnity of
                            £20,000, thereby removing all differences between the two Governments
                            and confirming their friendly relations.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Griscom is directed to ask that an early day be set for the payment
                            of the sum due, and to once more invite the attention of His Majesty and
                            of the Sublime Porte to the serious nature of the representations made
                            by him on April 24.]</p>
                    </div>
